And we proudly listened to victory on the radio 
from the

17:01.769 --> 17:15.906
European and Pacific theaters. Particularly, I 
remember D-Day, June 6, 1944. We were driving up to

17:26.655 --> 17:30.559
Garland to visit family. I kept the radio on almost 
all the trip in the car.

17:40.031 --> 17:45.437
And then my grandmother Jackson, mother's 
mother, my maternal grandmother Jackson,

17:47.290 --> 18:08.130
allowed me to sleep on a pallet in the living room of 
her farmhouse, and put the radio right down by my

17:47.290 --> 18:08.130
pallet, and I listened about almost all night to 
reports of the victory the Americans were

17:47.290 --> 18:08.130
attaining.

